<div id="review_2230434076" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2230434076" />
    <a title="Amanda" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/66887739-amanda"><img alt="Amanda" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1505529431p2/66887739.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2230434076?book_show_action=true">Dec 28, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Amanda" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Amanda" href="/user/show/66887739-amanda">Amanda</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2230434076" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1896176253508956676">This is one of the best short story collections. Generally I find short stories very incomplete and well (frankly) meaningless and so a bit of a waste of time. Bradbury, however is a master of the art. The stories in this collection all spoke volumes, were beautifully written and were incredibly thought provoking. I have definitely become a fan. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


